      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tariffs are a type of tax levied on imported goods, and their impact is debated. While they may protect domestic industries by raising prices on imported goods, making them less competitive, this protection often comes at the cost of increased prices for consumers, as higher import costs are passed on to them through higher retail prices. Additionally, tariffs can also lead to retaliatory measures from other countries, potentially triggering broader trade wars.",
